Instruction of running webrtc_unity_plugin on Winuwp Unity

Compilation must be done using visual-studio wrapper project at this time, with `WINUWP` preprocessor definition.
To learn more, and to find an existing visual studio wrapper, see https://github.com/webrtc-uwp/webrtc-windows/tree/master/projects/msvc.

After building, copy webrtc_unity_plugin under Assets/Plugins/WSA/x86_64 (or x86, depending on target architecture)

In Unity winuwp player settings, ensure the following capabilities are allowed:
+ InternetClient
+ InternetClientServer
+ PrivateNetworkClientServer
+ Webcam
+ Microphone
